    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "The owner of the Joyful Pastries Food Truck business wants to give a bonus to the food truck that had the most sales last week. The owner has a list of the daily sales each food truck made last week. They need to determine what the total sales were for each food truck so they can find which food truck had the most sales.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">FoodTruck</code> class, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">totalSales()</code> method to calculate and return the total sales for a food truck.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Owner</code> class, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">findMostSales()</code> method to determine which food truck has the most sales and returns the name of the food truck.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #3:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">FoodTruckRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">findMostSales()</code> method and print the result.",
